Class Description
BinaryOperations
Class saves binary data and reads binary data from a .BIN file The BinaryOperations class takes in the transactions as a list Object and saves the data to directory "Resources/UserData.Bin".

Class is used to display all transactions in ascending order of cost.
DisplayAllTransactionsDescendCost
Class is used to display all transactions in descending order of cost.
FileHandler
Class saves Object data in .CSV format and reads this data from a .CSV file * * The FileHandler class takes in the transactions * as a list object of type Transactions and saves the data to directory * "Resources/AllTransactions.csv".
Loggable
Interface specifies the methods that a Loggable program should have.
Logger
Abstract Class specified in broad outline that a class that extends this class should log data from a user and store data on a database The Logger abstract specifies in broad outline what the functions are that a class that inherits from the Logger abstract class should be able to perform.
Main
Class runs User Interface inside console The Main class takes in the transactions from the user via the console.
